Press Release These are indeed good times for the people of Ukanafun/Oruk Anam Federal Constituency as the Member representing the zone Hon. Unyime Idem is set to give account of his stewardship to his constituents. The Constituency briefing which is scheduled to hold on Monday December 23, 2019 by 9.00 at the Ukanafun/Oruk Anam Empowerment Centre, will provide the Telecoms Guru turned politician the platform to present his scorecard to the Federal Constituency, lay foundation for the construction of 2 Nos Skills Acquisition Centres in both Ukanafun and Oruk Anam L.G.As and share Christmas packages to the 24 wards that make up the Federal Constituency in line with the spirit of the season. He will also use the occasion to renew his pledge to the unity and development of Ukanafun/Oruk Anam Federal Constituency. Recall that barely few months after being inaugurated, the Deputy Chairman Communications Committee in Nigeria’s House of Representatives, held a Town Hall Meeting and flagged off skills acquisition and empowerment programme for 5000 of his constituents. He also publicly announced the donation of his four years salaries and allowances for the execution of the Empowerment Programme. The foundation laying for construction of two skills acquisition centres both in Ukanafun and Oruk Anam L.G.A.s being the latest effort at improving the lives of the people, is in keeping with Hon. Idem’s avowed commitment in helping to raise the next generation of business leaders who would be self-sufficient and contribute to the development of Akwa Ibom State and Nigeria. The public is hereby invited to grace this epoch-making event. Publicity Unit
Office of the Honourable Member Representing Ukanafun/Oruk Anam Federal Constituency in Nigeria’s House of Representatives. Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook 